JOHANNESBURG - Henri van Breda’s lawyers say they may be forced to abandon defending him, if the case faces further costly delays. The defence team opened its case on Monday, with a DNA expert challenging the State’s evidence. Van Breda has pleaded not guilty to killing his mother, father and brother. WATCH: Van Breda defence presents its case His younger sister, Marli, survived, but can’t remember the attack. "We are really at this moment, at a point where we may find ourselves to have to withdraw the defence of our client simply because he has run out of funds," said Pieter Botha, Defence Advocate. The case continues.  eNCA